Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createActiveLogicView(25.10)                      createActiveLogicView(25.10)

Name
       createActiveLogicView  -  Trims the timing graph to ignore logic inside
       the first level registers in partitions to improve runtime for  timing-
       related commands

Syntax
       createActiveLogicView

       [help]

       [-type {flatTop timingBudget topIO}[-setDontTouch | -unsetDontTouch ]]

       Trims the timing graph to ignore logic inside the first level registers
       in  partitions to improve runtime for timing-related commands. This ca-
       pability should only be used for timing analysis purpose.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes type and  default  in-
              formation for each createActiveLogicView parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man createActiveLogicView.

       -setDontTouch
              Sets  the  dontTouch  value as true. This freezes I/O interfaces
              (Interface logics and interface nets) and prevents  the   optDe-
              sign  -postCTS -hold from optimizing the block interface logics.
              The ILM ECO data can be loaded back.

       -type {flatTop timingBudget topIO}
              Specifies the Active Logic View type.

              * flatTop: Used to mark the top-level timing graph to  mask  all
                logic inside the interface logic of each partition.

              * timingBudget:  Instructs the command to use tuned settings for
                deriveTimingBudget when marking the top-level timing graph.

                This option should be specified if you plan to run  timeDesign
                or optVirtual with ART based and later on run deriveTimingBud-
                get based on the resulted timing graph.

              * topIO: Marks interface nets/instances to don't touch, so opti-
                mizer  will  preserve the I/O paths during optimization. Value
                of -topIO is -setDontTouch or -unsetDontTouch.

       -unsetDontTouch
              Sets dontTouch value as false. This resets the dontTouch on  I/O
              logics before reading the ECO data.

Related Information
              * clearActiveLogicView

              * timeDesign

              * optVirtual

              * deriveTimingBudget

              * Timing Analysis chapter of the Innovus User Guide

              * Top-level  Timing Closure Methodologies chapter of the Innovus
                User Guide

